          <p class="supertitle">Full Time / New York, NY</p>
  <h1>Web Engineer</h1>

  <div class="columns generic ">
    <div class="column main">
      <p>You must be looking for a fast-paced, challenging environment. Our sites are constantly changing to accommodate product vision, editorial needs, and user feedback. This is your opportunity to work with a highly skilled team of developers on cutting edge technologies.</p>

<h2>Requirements</h2>

<ul>
<li>2-4 years experience developing software applications in a commercial or institutional environment; agency experience is a plus.</li>
<li>Strong knowledge of PHP5, MySQL, Apache, jQuery, CSS, HTML</li>
<li>Experience with developing Facebook apps (FBML, FBJS, XFML etc)</li>
<li>Experience with creating and consuming RESTful APIs</li>
<li>Experience with CakePHP or other MVC frameworks</li>
<li>Self motivated, and be able to multitask</li>
<li>Strong object oriented programming knowledge</li>
</ul>


<h2>Qualities</h2>

<ul>
<li>Passionate and excited about technology, web scale architecture, social, mobile applications and content management systems</li>
<li>Enjoys working with the latest technologies, 3rd party applications, and social networking apps and wants to push the edge of web development</li>
<li>Believes the best applications can be developed inexpensively and have yet to be developed</li>
<li>Ability to drive projects through to completion on time/on budget, with or without supervision</li>
<li>Can communicate technical difficulties in a productive manner</li>
<li>Clear and useful code documentation</li>
<li>Aptitude for learning new technologies and adapting to changes in process or requirements</li>
<li>Can be part of or lead a collaborative team with excellent communication skills, creativity, and innovative thinking</li>
<li>Comfortable presenting complex technical ideas and business topics to team members and clients</li>
<li>Self starter/motivator; ownership and pride in your own work</li>
</ul>

</div><!-- /.column.main -->

